#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing <command>virt-v2v</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "The installation of <command>virt-v2v</command> is simple:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper install virt-v2v"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remember that <command>virt-v2v</command> requires &rootuser; privileges, so "
"you need to run it either as &rootuser;, or via <command>sudo</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conditions for Skipping This Step"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If running <command>virt-v2v</command> on &slsa; 12 SP1 or before, this step "
"can be safely skipped. This step can also be ignored if the virtual machine "
"is fully virtualized or if it runs on &slsa; 12 SP2 or later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &xen; virtual machine must have default kernel installed. To ensure "
"this, run <command>zypper in kernel-default</command> on the virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting Virtual Machines to Run under &kvm; Managed by &libvirt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> converts virtual machines from the &xen; "
"hypervisor to run under &kvm; managed by &libvirt;. To learn more about "
"&libvirt; and <command>virsh</command> , see <xref linkend=\"part.virt."
"libvirt\"/> . Additionally, all <command>virt-v2v</command> command line "
"options are explained in the <command>virt-v2v</command> manual page "
"( <command>man 1 virt-v2v</command> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:168
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before converting a virtual machine, make sure to complete the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the Environment for the Conversion"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new local storage pool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> copies the storage of the source virtual machine "
"to a local storage pool managed by &libvirt; (the original disk image "
"remains unchanged). You can create the pool either with &vmm;, or "
"<command>virsh</command> . For more information, see <xref linkend=\"sec."
"libvirt.storage.vmm\"/> and <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt.storage.virsh\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prepare the local network interface."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check that the converted virtual machine can use a local network interface "
"on the &vmhost;. It is usually a network bridge. If it is not defined yet, "
"create it with <menuchoice><guimenu>&yast;</guimenu><guimenu>System</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Network Settings</guimenu><guimenu>Add</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Bridge</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:199
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mappings of Network Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Network devices on the source &xen; host can be mapped during the conversion "
"process to corresponding network devices on the &kvm; target host. For "
"example, the &xen; bridge <literal>br0</literal> can be mapped to the KVM "
"network default. Sample mappings can be found in <filename>/etc/virt-v2v."
"conf</filename> . To enable these mappings, modify the XML rule as necessary "
"and ensure the section is not commented out with <literal>&lt;!--</literal> "
"and <literal>--&gt;</literal> markers. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" &lt;network type='bridge' name='br0'&gt;\n"
"   &lt;network type='network' name='default'/&gt;\n"
" &lt;/network&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid "No Network Bridge"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is no network bridge available, &vmm; can optionally create it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>virt-v2v</command> has the following basic command syntax:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"virt-v2v -i <replaceable>INPUT_METHOD</replaceable> -os "
"<replaceable>STORAGE_POOL</replaceable> <replaceable>SOURCE_VM</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "input_method"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two input methods: <literal>libvirt</literal> or "
"<literal>libvirtxml</literal> . See the <replaceable>SOURCE_VM</replaceable> "
"parameter for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "storage_pool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:243
#, no-c-format
msgid "The storage pool you already prepared for the target virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "source_vm"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The source virtual machine to convert. It depends on the "
"<replaceable>INPUT_METHOD</replaceable> parameter: For <literal>libvirt</"
"literal> , specify the name of a libvirt domain. For <literal>libvirtxml</"
"literal> , specify the path to an XML file containing a libvirt domain "
"specification."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conversion Time"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Conversion of a virtual machine takes a lot of system resources, mainly for "
"copying the whole disk image for a virtual machine. Converting a single "
"virtual machine typically takes up to 10 minutes, although virtual machines "
"using very large disk images can take much longer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:271
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conversion Based on the &libvirt; XML Description File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes how to convert a local &xen; virtual machine using "
"the &libvirt; XML configuration file. This method is suitable if the host is "
"already running the &kvm; hypervisor. Make sure that the &libvirt; XML file "
"of the source virtual machine, and the &libvirt; storage pool referenced "
"from it are available on the local host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obtain the &libvirt; XML description of the source virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:287
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obtaining the XML Files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To obtain the &libvirt; XML files of the source virtual machine, you must "
"run the host OS under the &xen; kernel. If you already rebooted the host to "
"the &kvm;-enabled environment, reboot back to the &xen; kernel, dump the "
"&libvirt; XML file, and then reboot back to the &kvm; environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:296
#, no-c-format
msgid "First identify the source virtual machine under virsh:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>sles12_xen</literal> is the source virtual machine to convert. Now "
"export its XML and save it to <filename>sles12_xen.xml</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;virsh dumpxml sles12_xen &gt; sles12_xen.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Verify all disk image paths are correct from the &kvm; host's perspective. "
"This is not a problem when converting on one machine, but may require manual "
"changes when converting using an XML dump from another host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;source file='/var/lib/libvirt/images/XenPool/SLES.qcow2'/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copying Images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid copying an image twice, manually copy the disk image(s) directly to "
"the &libvirt; storage pool. Update the source file entries in the XML "
"description file. The <command>virt-v2v</command> process will detect the "
"existing disks and convert them in place."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virt-v2v sles12_xen.xml<co xml:id=\"v2v.xml\"/> \\\n"
"-i <replaceable>LIBVIRTXML</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.method\"/> \\\n"
"-os <replaceable>remote_host.example.com:/exported_dir</replaceable><co xml:"
"id=\"v2v.pool\"/> \\\n"
"--bridge <replaceable>br0</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.bridge\"/> \\\n"
"-on <replaceable>sles12_kvm</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.name\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "The XML description of the source &xen;-based virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:347
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> will read the information about the source "
"virtual machine form a &libvirt; XML file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Storage pool where the target virtual machine disk image will be placed. In "
"this example, the image will be placed on an NFS share <filename>/"
"exported_dir</filename> on the <literal>remote_host.example.com</literal> "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The target &kvm;-based virtual machine will use the network bridge "
"<literal>br0</literal> on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:367
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The target virtual machine will be renamed to <literal>sles12_kvm</literal> "
"to prevent name collision with the existing virtual machine of the same name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conversion Based on the &libvirt; Domain Name"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This method is useful if you are still running &libvirt; under &xen;, and "
"plan to reboot to the &kvm; hypervisor later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find the &libvirt; domain name of the virtual machine you want to convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virsh list\n"
" Id    Name                           State\n"
"----------------------------------------------------\n"
"[...]\n"
"  2     sles12_xen                     running\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run <command>virt-v2v</command> to convert to &kvm; virtual machine:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virt-v2v sles12_xen<co xml:id=\"v2v.domain\"/> \\\n"
"-i <replaceable>libvirt</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.method1\"/> \\\n"
"-os <replaceable>storage_pool</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.pool1\"/> \\\n"
"--network <replaceable>eth0</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.net\"/> \\\n"
"-of qcow2<co xml:id=\"v2v.qcow\"/> \\\n"
"-oa sparce<co xml:id=\"v2v.sparse\"/> \\\n"
"-on <replaceable>sles12_kvm</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:414
#, no-c-format
msgid "The domain name of the &xen;-based virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> will read the information about the source "
"virtual machine directly from the active &libvirt; connection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "The target disk image will be placed in a local &libvirt; storage pool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All guest bridges (or networks) will be connected to a locally managed "
"network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Format for the disk image of the target virtual machine. Supported options "
"are <option>raw</option> or <option>qcow2</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the converted guest disk space will be <option>sparse</option> or "
"<option>preallocated</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:454
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting a Remote &xen; Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This method is useful if you need to convert a &xen; virtual machine running "
"on a remote host. As <command>virt-v2v</command> connects to the remote host "
"via <command>ssh</command> , ensure that SSH service is running on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid "Passwordless SSH Access"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &slsa; 12 SP2, <command>virt-v2v</command> requires a "
"passwordless SSH connection to the remote host. This means a connection "
"using an SSH key added to the ssh-agent. See <command>man ssh-keygen</"
"command> and <command>man ssh-add</command> for more details on this. More "
"information is also available at <xref linkend=\"cha.ssh\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To connect to a remote &libvirt; connection, construct a valid connection "
"URI relevant for your remote host. In the following example, the remote host "
"name is <literal>remote_host.example.com</literal> , and the user name for "
"the connection is &rootuser;. The connection URI then looks as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:480
#, no-c-format
msgid "xen+ssh://root@remote_host.example.com/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information on &libvirt; connection URIs, see <link xlink:href="
"\"http://libvirt.org/uri.html\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find the &libvirt; domain name of the remote virtual machine you want to "
"convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:491
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virsh -c xen+ssh://root@remote_host.example.com/ list\n"
" Id    Name                           State\n"
"----------------------------------------------------\n"
"  1     sles12_xen                     running\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>sles12_xen</literal> is the source virtual machine to convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>virt-v2v</command> command for the remote connection looks like "
"this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:506
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virt-v2v sles12_xen \\\n"
"-i <replaceable>libvirt</replaceable> \\\n"
"-ic <replaceable>xen+ssh://root@remote_host.example.com/</replaceable> \\\n"
"-os <replaceable>local_storage_pool</replaceable> \\\n"
"--bridge <replaceable>br0</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:517
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running Converted Virtual Machines"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:518
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After <command>virt-v2v</command> completes successfully, a new &libvirt; "
"domain will be created with the name specified with the <option>-on</option> "
"option. If you did not specify <option>-on</option> , the same name as the "
"source virtual machine will be used. The new guest can be managed with "
"standard &libvirt; tools, such as <command>virsh</command> or &vmm;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:527
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rebooting the Machine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you completed the conversion under &xen; as described in <xref linkend="
"\"x2k.v2v.convert.domain\"/> , you may need to reboot the host machine and "
"boot with the non-&xen; kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:537
#, no-c-format
msgid "&xen; to &kvm; Manual Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:542
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Outline"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preferred solution to manage virtual machines is based on &libvirt;; for "
"more information, see <link xlink:href=\"http://libvirt.org/\"/> . It has "
"several advantages over the manual way of defining and running virtual "
"machines&mdash;&libvirt; is cross-platform, supports many hypervisors, has "
"secure remote management, has virtual networking, and, most of all, provides "
"a unified abstract layer to manage virtual machines. Therefore the main "
"focus of this article is on the &libvirt; solution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generally, the &xen; to &kvm; migration runs in the following basic steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:560
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make a backup copy of the original &xen; &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:565
#, no-c-format
msgid "OPTIONAL: Apply changes specific to paravirtualized guests."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Obtain information about the original &xen; &vmguest; and update it to &kvm; "
"equivalents."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shut down the guest on the &xen; host, and run the new one under the &kvm; "
"hypervisor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:583
#, no-c-format
msgid "No Live Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &xen; to &kvm; migration cannot be done live while the source &vmguest; "
"is running. Before running the new &kvm;-ready &vmguest;, you are advised to "
"shut down the original &xen; &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "Back Up the &xen; &vmguest;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:595
#, no-c-format
msgid "To back up your &xen; &vmguest;, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identify the relevant &xen; guest you want to migrate, and remember its ID/"
"name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:604
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;virsh list --all\n"
"Id Name                 State\n"
"----------------------------------\n"
" 0 Domain-0             running\n"
" 1 SLES11SP3            running\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:612
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shut down the guest. You can do this either by shutting down the guest OS, "
"or with <command>virsh</command> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:616
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;virsh shutdown SLES11SP3"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backup its configuration to an XML file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:622
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;virsh dumpxml SLES11SP3 &gt; sles11sp3.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Backup its disk image file. Use the <command>cp</command> or <command>rsync</"
"command> commands to create the backup copy. Remember that it is always a "
"good idea to check the copy with the <command>md5sum</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:633
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the image file is backed up, you can start the guest again with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:636
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;virsh start SLES11SP3"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:642
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changes Specific to Paravirtualized Guests"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:643
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apply the following changes if you are migrating a paravirtualized &xen; "
"guest. You can do it either on the running guest, or on the stopped guest "
"using <literal>guestfs-tools</literal> . <!-- toba: maybe add more info on "
"guestfs-tools -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After applying the changes described in this section, the image file related "
"to the migrated &vmguest; will not be usable under &xen; anymore."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install the Default Kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:659
#, no-c-format
msgid "No Booting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:660
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you installed the default kernel, do not try to boot the &xen; guest "
"with it, the system will not boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before cloning the &xen; guest disk image for use under the &kvm; "
"hypervisor, make sure it is bootable <emphasis>without</emphasis> the &xen; "
"hypervisor. This is very important for paravirtualized &xen; guests as they "
"usually contain a special &xen; kernel, and often do not have a complete "
"&grub; boot loader installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &slsa; 11 update the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/kernel</filename> file. "
"Change the <literal>INITRD_MODULES</literal> parameter by removing all &xen; "
"drivers and replacing the with virtio drivers. Replace"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "INITRD_MODULES=\"xenblk xennet\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:684
#, no-c-format
msgid "INITRD_MODULES=\"virtio_blk virtio_pci virtio_net virtio_balloon\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &slsa; 12 search for <literal>xenblk xennet</literal> in <filename>/etc/"
"dracut.conf.d/*.conf</filename> and replace them with <literal>virtio_blk "
"virtio_pci virtio_net virtio_balloon</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Paravirtualized &xen; guests are running a specific &xen; kernel. To run the "
"guest under &kvm;, you need to install the default kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:697
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default Kernel Is Already Installed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You do not need to install the default kernel for a fully virtualized guests "
"as it is already installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter <command>rpm -q kernel-default</command> on the &xen; guest to find "
"out if the default kernel is installed. If not, install it with "
"<command>zypper in kernel-default</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The kernel we are going to use to boot the guest under &kvm; must have "
"<emphasis>virtio</emphasis> (paravirtualized) drivers available. Run the "
"following command to find out. Do not forget to replace <literal>3.8.9-4</"
"literal> with your kernel version:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;find /lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/ -name "
"virtio*\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/net/virtio_net.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/scsi/virtio_scsi.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/block/virtio_blk.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/char/virtio_console.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/char/hw_random/virtio-rng.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_pci.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_balloon.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_ring.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_mmio.ko"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:728
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> . Change any storage devices from "
"<literal>xvda</literal> to <literal>vda</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:734
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update the boot loader configuration. Enter <command>rpm -q grub2</command> "
"on the &xen; guest to find out if &grub; is already installed. If not, "
"install it with <command>zypper in grub2</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now make the newly installed default kernel the default for booting the OS. "
"Also remove/update the kernel command line options that may refer to &xen;-"
"specific devices. You can do it either with &yast; "
"( <menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu><guimenu>Boot Loader</guimenu></"
"menuchoice> ), or manually:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:749
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find the preferred Linux boot menu entry by listing them all:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:752
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;cat /boot/grub2/grub.cfg | grep 'menuentry '"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:753
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remember the order number (counted from zero) of the one you newly installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:759
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set it the default boot menu entry:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:762
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;grub2-set-default <replaceable>N</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:763
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>N</replaceable> with the number of the boot menu entry "
"you previously discovered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:769
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open <filename>/etc/default/grub</filename> for editing, and look for "
"<option>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT</option> and "
"<option>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_RECOVERY</option> options. Remove/update any "
"reference to &xen;-specific devices. In the following example, you can "
"replace"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:776
#, no-c-format
msgid "root=/dev/xvda1 disk=/dev/xvda console=xvc"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:777
#, no-c-format
msgid "with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:780
#, no-c-format
msgid "root=/dev/vda1 disk=/dev/vda"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:781
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that you need to remove all references to <literal>xvc</literal> -type "
"consoles (such as <literal>xvc0</literal> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update <filename>device.map</filename> in one of <filename>/boot/grub2</"
"filename> or <filename>/boot/grub2-efi</filename> directories. Change any "
"storage device from <literal>xvda</literal> to <literal>vda</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:798
#, no-c-format
msgid "To import new default settings, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:801
#, no-c-format
msgid "grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:806
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the Guest for Boot under &kvm;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update the system to use default serial console. List the configured "
"consoles, and remove symbolic links to <literal>xvc?</literal> ones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;ls -l /etc/systemd/system/getty.target.wants/\n"
"getty@tty1.service -&gt; /usr/lib/systemd/system/getty@.service\n"
"getty@xvc0.service -&gt; /usr/lib/systemd/system/getty@xvc0.service\n"
"getty@xvc1.service -&gt; /usr/lib/systemd/system/getty@xvc1.service\n"
"\n"
"# rm /etc/systemd/system/getty.target.wants/getty@xvc?.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:821
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update the <filename>/etc/securetty</filename> file. Replace <literal>xvc0</"
"literal> with <literal>ttyS0</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:831
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the &xen; &vmguest; Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:832
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes how to export the configuration of the original &xen; "
"&vmguest;, and what particular changes to apply to it so it can be imported "
"as a &kvm; guest into &libvirt;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:838
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export the &xen; &vmguest; Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First export the configuration of the guest and save it to a file. A typical "
"one may look like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:843
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;virsh dumpxml SLES11SP3\n"
"&lt;domain type='xen'&gt;\n"
"  &lt;name&gt;SLES11SP3&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"  &lt;uuid&gt;fa9ea4d7-8f95-30c0-bce9-9e58ffcabeb2&lt;/uuid&gt;\n"
"  &lt;memory&gt;524288&lt;/memory&gt;\n"
"  &lt;currentMemory&gt;524288&lt;/currentMemory&gt;\n"
"  &lt;vcpu&gt;1&lt;/vcpu&gt;\n"
"  &lt;bootloader&gt;/usr/bin/pygrub&lt;/bootloader&gt;\n"
"  &lt;os&gt;\n"
"    &lt;type&gt;linux&lt;/type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/os&gt;\n"
"  &lt;clock offset='utc'/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;on_poweroff&gt;destroy&lt;/on_poweroff&gt;\n"
"  &lt;on_reboot&gt;restart&lt;/on_reboot&gt;\n"
"  &lt;on_crash&gt;restart&lt;/on_crash&gt;\n"
"  &lt;devices&gt;\n"
"    &lt;emulator&gt;/usr/lib/xen/bin/qemu-dm&lt;/emulator&gt;\n"
"    &lt;disk type='file' device='disk'&gt;\n"
"      &lt;driver name='file'/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;source file='/var/lib/libvirt/images/SLES_11_SP2_JeOS."
"x86_64-0.0.2_para.raw'/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;target dev='xvda' bus='xen'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/disk&gt;\n"
"    &lt;interface type='bridge'&gt;\n"
"      &lt;mac address='00:16:3e:2d:91:c3'/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;source bridge='br0'/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script path='vif-bridge'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/interface&gt;\n"
"    &lt;console type='pty'&gt;\n"
"      &lt;target type='xen' port='0'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/console&gt;\n"
