#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:878
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can find detailed information on the libvirt XML format for &vmguest; "
"description at <link xlink:href=\"http://libvirt.org/formatdomain.html\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:885
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Changes to the Guest Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:886
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need to make a few general changes to the exported &xen; guest XML "
"configuration to run it under the &kvm; hypervisor. The following applies to "
"both fully virtualized and paravirtualized guests. Note that not all of the "
"following XML elements need to be in your specific configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:894
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conventions Used"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To refer to a node in the XML configuration file, an XPath syntax will be "
"used throughout this document. For example, to refer to a <literal>&lt;"
"name&gt;</literal> inside the <literal>&lt;domain&gt;</literal> tag"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:901
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;domain&gt;\n"
"  &lt;name&gt;sles11sp3&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"&lt;/domain&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:904
#, no-c-format
msgid "an XPath equivalent <literal>/domain/name</literal> will be used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>type</literal> attribute of the <literal>/domain</"
"literal> element from <literal>xen</literal> to <literal>kvm</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:917
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove the <literal>/domain/bootloader</literal> element section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:922
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove the <literal>/domain/bootloader_args</literal> element section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>/domain/os/type</literal> element value from "
"<literal>linux</literal> to <literal>hvm</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:934
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add <literal>&lt;boot dev=\"hd\"/&gt;</literal> under the <literal>/domain/"
"os</literal> element."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:940
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the <literal>arch</literal> attribute to the <literal>/domain/os/type</"
"literal> element. Acceptable values are <literal>arch=”x86_64”</literal> or "
"<literal>arch=”i686”</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>/domain/devices/emulator</literal> element from "
"<literal>/usr/lib/xen/bin/qemu-dm'</literal> to <literal>/usr/bin/qemu-kvm</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:955
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each disk associated with the paravirtualized (PV) guest, change the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:961
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>name</literal> attribute of the <literal>/domain/devices/"
"disk/driver</literal> element from <literal>file</literal> to <literal>qemu</"
"literal> , and add a <literal>type</literal> attribute for the disk type. "
"For example, valid options include <literal>raw</literal> or <literal>qcow2</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:971
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>dev</literal> attribute of the <literal>/domain/devices/"
"disk/target</literal> element from <literal>xvda</literal> to <literal>vda</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:978
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>bus</literal> attribute of the <literal>/domain/devices/"
"disk/target</literal> element from <literal>xen</literal> to "
"<literal>virtio</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:987
#, no-c-format
msgid "For each network interface card, do the following changes:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:992
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is <literal>model</literal> defined in <literal>/domain/devices/"
"interface</literal> , change its <literal>type</literal> attribute value to "
"<literal>virtio</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:998
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;model type=”virtio”&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1001
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Delete all <literal>/domain/devices/interface/script</literal> sections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1007
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Delete all <literal>/domain/devices/interface/target</literal> elements if "
"the <literal>dev</literal> attribute starts with <literal>vif</literal> or "
"<literal>vnet</literal> or <literal>veth</literal> . If using a custom "
"network then change the <literal>dev</literal> value to that target."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1018
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remove the <literal>/domain/devices/console</literal> element section if it "
"exists."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1024
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remove the <literal>/domain/devices/serial</literal> element section if it "
"exists."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1030
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <literal>bus</literal> attribute on the <literal>/domain/devices/"
"input</literal> element from <literal>xen</literal> to <literal>ps2</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1037
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the following element for memory ballooning features under the <literal>/"
"domain/devices</literal> element."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1041
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;memballoon model=\"virtio\"/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1045
#, no-c-format
msgid "Device Name"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1046
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>&lt;target dev='hda' bus='ide'/&gt;</literal> controls the device "
"under which the disk is exposed to the guest OS. The <literal>dev</literal> "
"attribute indicates the \"logical\" device name. The actual device name "
"specified is not guaranteed to map to the device name in the guest OS. "
"Therefore you may need to change the disk mapping on the boot loader command "
"line. For example, if the boot loader expects a root disk to be "
"<literal>hda2</literal> but &kvm; still sees it as <literal>sda2</literal> , "
"change the boot loader command line from"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1057
#, no-c-format
msgid "[...] root=/dev/hda2 resume=/dev/hda1 [...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1058
#, no-c-format
msgid "to"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1061
#, no-c-format
msgid "[...] root=/dev/sda2 resume=/dev/sda1 [...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1062
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the case of paravirtualized <literal>xvda</literal> devices, change it to"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1066
#, no-c-format
msgid "[...] root=/dev/vda2 resume=/dev/vda1 [...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1067
#, no-c-format
msgid "Otherwise the &vmguest; will refuse to boot in the &kvm; environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1074
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Target &kvm; Guest Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1075
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having applied all the modifications mentioned above, you end up with "
"the following configuration for your &kvm; guest:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:1079
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&lt;domain type='kvm'&gt;\n"
"  &lt;name&gt;SLES11SP3&lt;/name&gt;\n"
